    <div class="description">
        <h1 class="maintitle">Culture</h1>
        <hr class="main_ruler">
        <p>When first coming to Finland, some situations that seem mundane in our daily lives back at home, might get less obvious. For example, in Finland, people tend to be helpful but quite reserved – so things like chitchatting on the way to work, hugging or kissing as greetings, or talking about personal stuff can be challenging and even interpreted as intrusive by a local. We have selected some interesting sources to help you get familiar with the Finnish culture. Some of them are cracking-up funny – especially after you are living here for a while – others are as valuable as gold if you know close to nothing about Finland. One thing is for sure, there is no culture like this one – Finns are one of the most resilient, honest and peculiar high-tech tribes you will ever know.</p>
