    <div class="slideshow">
        <div class="slide_image" id="slide-1" style="background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)), url('images/Coffee.jpg')">
            <p>Finland has the highest coffee consumption in the world. The average Finn drinks about 12kg of coffee per year!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide_image" id="slide-2" style="background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)), url('images/Voting.jpg')">
        <p>In 1906, Finland became the first country in Europe to give women from all levels of society the right to vote and stand for parliament.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide_image" id="slide-3" style="background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)), url('images/Gender.jpg')">
        <p>Finnish is a gender neutral language, which is well shown by the third person singular pronoun <em>hän</em> (usually he or she in English) that can be used to refer a person of any gender.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide_image" id="slide-4" style="background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)), url('images/Lake.jpg')">
        <p>Finland is often called ‘the land of a thousand lakes’ but in reality it has over 188.000 of them, spread through its area of 338.440 km2.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide_image" id="slide-5" style="background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)), url('images/Flag.jpg')">
        <p>Despite its unique history, Finland is relatively young as an independent country. After being part of the Kingdom of Sweden and the Russian Empire, independence was declared in 1917.</p>
        </div>
